  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>La Pergola Restaurant </strong>is a casual restaurant with a modern feel. It offers traditional Sardinian and Mediterranean food.</p>
<p><strong>Le Dune Restaurant</strong> is located next to Campana Beach and has a relaxed, authentic feel. Dishes like grilled fish, fresh pasta and pizzas cooked in a wood-fired oven are served during lunch and dinner.</p>
<p><strong>Bioaquam Restaurant</strong> is exclusive to guests of the resort and offers healthier food while boasting views over the bay.</p>
<p><strong>La Terrazza Restaurant</strong> is a fine dining restaurant featuring delicious Italian specialities that can be enjoyed on the elegant terrace that looks out over the sea.</p>
<p><strong>Club House Restaurant</strong> is set next to the resort’s main pool and serves traditional Sardinian fare in a contemporary environment.</p>
<p><strong>Bouganville Restaurant</strong> offers themed buffets with the finest ingredients on the island. Expect locally-grown organic vegetables and main courses that are prepared by the chef’s in their live cooking shows.</p>
<p><strong>Whiteluna Restaurant</strong> has a more intimate atmosphere with a fine selection of Mediterranean dishes served alongside an extensive wine list.</p>
<p><strong>The Pizzeria</strong> is located in the Piazza Ulivi and has a traditional wood-fired oven to create fresh pizzas that can be enjoyed al fresco while soaking up the square’s energetic atmosphere.</p>
<p><strong>Panino </strong>offers simple yet delicious snacks. Enjoy sandwiches made from freshly-baked bread and fresh ingredients. You can even enjoy them on the beach with a dedicated delivery service.</p>
<p><strong>Bimbi Restaurant</strong> is a fun restaurant exclusively for children. Healthy and tasty dishes are served for lunch and dinner with buffet stations and tables designed just for kids.</p>
<p>Some restaurants may be open seasonally.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Swimming Pools</strong></span></p>
<p><em>There’s five pools at Chia Laguna Resort, including one that’s perfect for families and some dedicated to guests of certain hotels, so you’re sure to find your perfect poolside spot.</em></p>
<p><strong>Club House Pool</strong> is the largest and is located in the heart of Chia Laguna Resort. You’ll find plenty of sunloungers and umbrellas, as well as the Club House Restaurant for light lunches and refreshments during the day.</p>
<p><strong>Baia Pool</strong> is one of the newest additions to Chia’s pool scene and is reserved for guests of Hotel Baia. It’s surrounded by Mediterranean vegetation and has a 25 metre long freshwater pool with a shallow area dedicated to children.</p>
<p><strong>Bioaquam Pool</strong> is exclusively for guests staying at the five-star Hotel Laguna and has splendid views over the sea and bay of Chia. A spacious sun deck has comfortable loungers and there’s a pool bar on hand for light snacks and drinks.</p>
<p><strong>Oasi Pool</strong> offers a tranquil space, surrounded by lush gardens. Guests at Hotel Oasi will have this lovely pool right on their doorstep.</p>
<p><strong>Bambini Pool</strong> is ideal for young children with shallow waters and plenty of games to keep them entertained during the day.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Beaches</strong></span></p>
<p>Chia Laguna’s position means it’s close to some of the most beautiful beaches in Sardinia. Picture-perfect white sands lead to impossibly clear waters making it the ideal resort for beach lovers. Chia Beach is a protected natural landscape and boasts beautiful sand dunes as well as a flock of resident flamingos, it’s reached by Chia’s train that runs to and from the resort. The hotel also has reserved areas at Dunes di Campana, a stunning stretch of coastline surrounded dunes and wildflowers, and Cogoni beach, which is set in a bay and accessed by a path through the rocks.</p>
<p>Hotel Baia offers beach services (sunbeds, sun umbrella) at Monte Cogoni beach from third row. Guests staying in Suite Incanto rooms and Suites have beach services included in first row and people staing in Baia Prestige Mare Rooms have beach services included in second row.</p>
<p>There are also several other nearby beaches to choose from, try Su Giudeu for secluded white sands or Piscinni Beach that has small inlets and rock formations making it perfect for snorkelling.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<p>The more active will appreciate the huge range of sports and activities available at Chia Laguna Resort. There’s two red clay tennis courts with lessons available and mountain bikes are available to hire with plenty of stunning trails easily accessible from the resort that are also ideal for hiking or running. You can do these alone or join an organised group.</p>
<p>Other activities include horse riding along the beach, a nearby golf course and watersports like windsurfing and kayaking.</p>
<p>Activities are payable locally.</p>
<p><strong><u>Bars &amp; Nightlife</u></strong></p>
<p>Evenings at Chia Laguna Resort can be as lively or relaxed as you wish. The vibrant Piazza degli Ulivi puts on fantastic cabaret shows and live music, with restaurants and bars on hand for relaxed family dinners. For a more sophisticated affair, Whiteluna Lounge Bar plays live music in a refined and stylish setting. There’s six other bars to choose from too, including the romantic champagne bar on the terrace of Hotel Laguna.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Chia Natural Spa</strong></span></p>
<p>The spa at Chia Laguna Resort offers an array of treatments and facilities, and is the perfect place to spend a relaxing day. You’ll find three hydro-massage pools outside on a panoramic terrace with sea views. The interior is equipped with Turkish baths, saunas and energising showers. Choose to indulge in a facial or a massage, or sign up to a programme to experience a range of complementary treatments.</p>
<p>Entry to the spa and treatments are payable locally.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>General Facilities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Bus/shuttle service: Links rooms with reception and the hotel with the beach</li>
<li>Free wifi</li>
<li>Free use of the gym club</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
